# Keep `railway up` uploads to source only. The Railway CLI does not reliably
# honor .gitignore, so without this it tars the ~488M local .venv (plus caches
# and DB backups) and the upload fails mid-stream. The builder recreates the
# environment from pyproject/uv.lock, so none of this is needed remotely.
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
backups/
.git/
